# S01-T03: Flexible CSS Token Design System

## Objective
Build a flexible, token-driven design system using the proven navitrack pattern: **CSS variables (HSL) as single source of truth → Tailwind config mapping → component classes**. All tokens from `UI_REGULATION.ti`, architecture from navitrack.

## Architecture Pattern (from navitrack)
```
index.css (entry point)
  @import './styles/tokens.css'      ← HSL CSS variables (THE source of truth)
  @import './styles/tactical.css'    ← HUD-specific component classes
  @import './styles/touch.css'       ← Touch utilities (port from navitrack)
  @import './styles/layout.css'      ← Global html/body/root reset
  @tailwind base;
  @tailwind components;
  @tailwind utilities;
```

## Acceptance Criteria

### 1. CSS Tokens (`src/shared/styles/tokens.css`)
Single source of truth. ALL design decisions as CSS custom properties:

```css
:root {
  /* === Background Scale === */
  --hud-bg-dark: 163 55% 7%;         /* #071D1B */
  --hud-bg-medium: 163 45% 9%;       /* #0B2522 */
  --hud-bg-light: 163 36% 12%;       /* #102F2B */

  /* === Primary Accent (Cyan) === */
  --hud-cyan: 164 78% 45%;           /* #1ACDB3 */
  --hud-cyan-bright: 164 90% 55%;    /* #27F5D1 */
  --hud-cyan-dim: 164 78% 45% / 0.3;

  /* === Alert (Pink) === */
  --hud-pink: 340 75% 40%;           /* #B31A5A */
  --hud-pink-bright: 340 100% 65%;   /* #FF4D94 */

  /* === Warning (Amber) === */
  --hud-amber: 32 100% 65%;          /* #FFB84D */

  /* === Success (Green) === */
  --hud-green: 155 100% 65%;         /* #4DFFB8 */

  /* === Semantic === */
  --background: var(--hud-bg-dark);
  --foreground: 155 22% 76%;         /* muted green-white text */
  --primary: var(--hud-cyan);
  --primary-foreground: var(--hud-bg-dark);
  --destructive: var(--hud-pink);
  --border: var(--hud-cyan-dim);

  /* === Component Tokens === */
  --hud-panel-bg: 163 42% 7% / 0.9;  /* rgba(10,30,28,0.9) */
  --hud-border: 164 78% 45% / 0.3;   /* rgba(26,205,179,0.3) */
  --hud-border-hover: 164 78% 45% / 0.5;
  --hud-glow-cyan: 0 0 10px hsl(164 78% 45% / 0.6);
  --hud-glow-pink: 0 0 10px hsl(340 75% 40% / 0.6);

  /* === Touch (from navitrack) === */
  --touch-min: 48px;
  --touch-target-rec: 56px;
  --touch-icon: 24px;

  /* === Layout === */
  --radius: 4px;
  --radius-lg: 8px;

  /* === Motion === */
  --transition-fast: 150ms ease-out;
  --transition-base: 200ms ease-out;
  --transition-slow: 260ms ease-out;
}
```

### 2. Tailwind Config (`tailwind.config.ts`)
Map CSS variables to Tailwind utilities (navitrack pattern):

```typescript
colors: {
  background: 'hsl(var(--background))',
  foreground: 'hsl(var(--foreground))',
  primary: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--primary))', foreground: 'hsl(var(--primary-foreground))' },
  destructive: { DEFAULT: 'hsl(var(--destructive))' },
  hud: {
    'bg-dark': 'hsl(var(--hud-bg-dark))',
    'bg-medium': 'hsl(var(--hud-bg-medium))',
    'bg-light': 'hsl(var(--hud-bg-light))',
    cyan: 'hsl(var(--hud-cyan))',
    'cyan-bright': 'hsl(var(--hud-cyan-bright))',
    pink: 'hsl(var(--hud-pink))',
    'pink-bright': 'hsl(var(--hud-pink-bright))',
    amber: 'hsl(var(--hud-amber))',
    green: 'hsl(var(--hud-green))',
    panel: 'hsl(var(--hud-panel-bg))',
  },
  border: 'hsl(var(--border))',
}
```

### 3. Touch Utilities (`src/shared/styles/touch.css`)
Port from navitrack's touch.css (137 lines):
- `.touch-min`, `.touch-target`, `.touch-target-rec` classes
- `.safe-bottom`, `.safe-top` utilities
- Touch area expander (`::before` trick)
- Momentum scrolling, scrollbar-hide

### 4. Layout Reset (`src/shared/styles/layout.css`)
Port from navitrack:
- Hidden scrollbars globally
- `html, body`: 100dvh, overflow hidden, no overscroll
- `#root`: flex column, relative
- `touch-action: manipulation` on buttons
- `user-select: none` on body (except inputs)

### 5. Typography
JetBrains Mono + IBM Plex Mono loaded via Google Fonts link in `index.html`.
Set as Tailwind `fontFamily.mono`.

### 6. GPU Utility
```css
.gpu { transform: translateZ(0); will-change: transform; backface-visibility: hidden; }
```

### Why This Is Better Than Tailwind 4 CSS-only
- **navitrack ships to iOS/Android App Store** with this exact pattern — production-proven
- `tailwind.config.ts` gives full TypeScript control over the theme
- HSL CSS variables enable runtime theme changes (future: day/night modes)
- Mature plugin ecosystem (`tailwindcss-animate`)
- Components use clean Tailwind classes: `bg-hud-cyan text-foreground border-border`

## Anti-Patterns (from UI_REGULATION.ti)
- ❌ No glassmorphism / backdrop-blur on HUD panels (navitrack's glass.css NOT ported)
- ❌ No rounded-xl or rounded-full on panels
- ❌ No gradient backgrounds on panels
- ❌ No thick shadows

## Steps
1. Create `src/shared/styles/tokens.css` with all HSL variables
2. Create `tailwind.config.ts` with variable mapping
3. Port `touch.css` from navitrack (adjust min targets to 48px)
4. Port `layout.css` from navitrack (adjust for HUD transparent bg)
5. Create `index.css` with import chain
6. Add JetBrains Mono font in `index.html`
7. Verify all `bg-hud-*`, `text-hud-*`, `border-hud-*` classes work in browser
